#X text 24 269 The [rmstodb] object does the opposite conversion \,
where 1e-05 "RMS" amplitude corresponds to 0 dB. Values below 1e-05
down to 0 would output negative values (where 0 corresponds to minus
infinity dB) \, but these are clipped to 0 dB instead. Note that "RMS"
is misleading because the linear amplitude value maey refer to "peak"
amplitude as well. Also \, RMS can be equally be measured in dB.,
f 70;
